# Project VibeSummary: Bakaboria

Bakaboria is a Next.js application that integrates MongoDB (Mongoose) and Gemini 2.5 Flash (`@google/genai` API) to upload, search, process, and download document PDFs (stored locally or proxy-downloaded from Google Drive).

---

## 🛠️ Technology Stack
*   **Framework**: Next.js 15+ (App Router)
*   **Language**: TypeScript
*   **Database**: MongoDB via Mongoose
*   **Authentication**: NextAuth (Google OAuth + Credentials flow with plaintext passwords)
*   **Styling**: TailwindCSS
*   **AI Integration**: Google GenAI SDK (`@google/genai`), using `gemini-2.5-flash`

---

## 📂 Codebase Structure & Key Files

### 🛡️ Routing & Auth Middleware
*   **[middleware.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/middleware.ts)**: Intercepts requests on Edge runtime. Protects `/upload_doc` and `/get_doc`, redirecting unauthenticated users to `/signIn`.
*   **[app/auth.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/auth.config.ts)**: Configures the Google OAuth provider and basic authorized check callback.
*   **[app/auth.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/auth.ts)**: Implements NextAuth with both Google OAuth and a custom Credentials provider. It upserts users into MongoDB on sign-in, links their Mongo `_id` to the session JWT, and implements registration of new users when checking credentials.

### 💾 Database Connection & Models (`models/`)
*   **[lib/db.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/lib/db.ts)**: Connects to MongoDB (uses `MONGODB_URI` from `.env.local` or defaults to `mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/school`).
*   **[models/users.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/models/users.ts)**: Defines `userSchema` / `userModel`. Stores `uid` (string), `username`, `email`, `password` (plaintext, optional), `image` (Google avatar, optional), and `role` (default: "user").
*   **[models/Document.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/models/Document.ts)**: Defines the `DocumentSchema` / `DocumentModel` for uploaded files. Fields:
    *   `uid`: Owner user ID
    *   `name`: Document title
    *   `password`: (Optional) Access password
    *   `tags`: Base tags (e.g. subject, department)
    *   `primaryTags`, `propertyTags`: Categorization tags
    *   `hidden`: Boolean visibility flag
    *   `hiddenTags`: Tags that unlock access to hidden documents
    *   `processed`, `reviewed`: Gemini analysis status flags
    *   `fileLocation`: Drive URL or local path
    *   `fileName`, `fileSize`, `mimeType`, `verified`
    *   `storeMethod`: `"PDF"` (local storage under `docus/`) or `"DRIVE"` (Google Drive)
*   **[models/GeminiResult.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/models/GeminiResult.ts)**: Defines `GeminiResultSchema` mapping `_id` (1:1 with Document `_id`) to a parsed JSON `result` object containing exam structural metrics.
*   **[models/Hierarchy.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/models/Hierarchy.ts)**: Defines `HierarchySchema` / `HierarchyModel` to map parent/child node relationships. Fields include `Name` (string), `tag_Name` (unique string), `parents` array (with `p-name` and `p-id`), and `children` array (matching parent structure).

### 🧠 Gemini Integration (`lib/gemini.ts`)
*   **[lib/gemini.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/lib/gemini.ts)**: Contains the core Gemini logic:
    1.  Downloads/retrieves the PDF file (either locally from `docus/` or proxied from Google Drive via direct download link).
    2.  Sends the base64-encoded PDF to `gemini-2.5-flash` with a custom prompt (`PROMPT`) instructing it to extract structural features: exam length, total marks, section types, cognitive distribution (recall vs. calculation vs. design/troubleshoot), topic weighting, scenarios blacklist, and a high-fidelity list of all questions (`exam_content`).
    3.  Enforces a strict structured output schema (`RESPONSE_SCHEMA`) via `responseMimeType: "application/json"`.
    4.  Stores the parsed result in the `GeminiResult` collection mapping to the document ID.

