## 🌐 API Routes (`app/api/`)

*   **[app/api/upload/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/api/upload/route.ts)**: Handles document registration.
    *   *Drive Mode*: Extracts File ID from Google Drive share link, calculates size via a `HEAD` request, and stores the Document metadata in MongoDB.
    *   *PDF Mode*: Writes the uploaded file buffer to the local `docus/` folder under a collision-free filename, registering it in MongoDB.
*   **[app/api/documents/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/api/documents/route.ts)**: Fetches and filters documents by `name` or `tags` (combining terms split by `#`). Filters out hidden documents unless a searched tag matches one of the document's `hiddenTags`. Returns a list with `password` omitted (but sets `hasPassword` indicator).
*   **[app/api/download/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/api/download/route.ts)**: Receives a document `id` and `password`. If password matches the database, it returns a binary PDF payload. For Drive files, it proxies/buffers Google Drive's download endpoint to serve the PDF directly to the client.
*   **[app/api/gemini/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/api/gemini/route.ts)**: POST endpoint taking a document ID to execute the Gemini analysis pipeline (`processWithGemini`).
*   **[app/api/hierarchy/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/api/hierarchy/route.ts)**: POST endpoint processing terminal input commands (`root`, `navigate`, `create <Name> <tag_Name>`, `id`, `adopt <ID>`, `custody <ID> [?name]`, `disown <ID>`, `guardian <ID>`, `destroy <ID> [?name] [-all]`, and node selection navigation / `cd`). Auto-seeds demo nodes (`CUFE`, `BUE`, `MEC`, etc.) on first boot if the database is empty.
*   **[app/api/migrate-documents/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/AIO12TH-RTX30WHITE/bakaboria/app/api/migrate-documents/route.ts)**: Maintenance route that sets default values (empty lists / false) on older documents for newly introduced database properties.

